This place is very clean and cute, a cozy lazy vibe restaurant. Our favorite is New Orleans BBQ Chicken. It reminds me hometown bbq chicken when I was young, especially with that small bags of black peppers. They will give you a pair of plastic hand bags so you can eat it as a King/Queen. However the squid rings is not very good, unfortunately. Some of the items are a bit overpriced. Overall, we will still back for the New Orleans BBQ. Yummy!
